race.comment: TACTFULL (12) doesn't win out of turn but is worth another try here. Close to the winner two on end including a close-up third ninth Traralgon Cup two back, then caught off the track throughout last time. Back in grade and gets chance to find winning form. TAKEMETOTHEMOON (9) is the clear danger. Raced on speed over a mile fresh and went down narrowly, and can only be fitter for the extra ground. The stable always have then ready early and no surprise to see a return to winning form. DANCING JUICE (7) is mixing form, finishing an eye-catching second two back before a terrible run last time. Best figures stack up and worth another try. NORTHWOOD VAMOOSE (10) is another struggling for best but rates highly on best figures and gets chance to find some form in this easier grade. OUTCASTER (13) has a decent record this course and can also do better this level.
